<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<%- include('head'); -%>

<body>
  <div class="wrap">
    <%- include('header'); -%>
    <h1>Ahey - a free video chat app for the web.</h1>
    <section>
      <p>
        Ahey is a frictionless, peer-to-peer video conferencing app you can use right in your browser - no sign-ups,
        no downloads, 100% free. Create public rooms to meet new people and not just your friends.
      </p>
      <p>
        Just share your room URL and connect instantly.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div id="roombox" class="flex">
        <span class="domain">ahey.net/</span>
        <input type="text" placeholder="room-id" class="flex-1" />
        <button onClick="onJoin()">Start</button>
      </div>
      <div class="small light">Entering a room id is optional - click "Start" to generate a random room. Start the room id with "@" to make it public.</div>
      <br />
    </section>

    <section>
      <a href="/public" class="public-cta flex">
        <span class="flex-1">
          <strong>Find public rooms</strong>
          <div class="small light">Meet random people in open, discoverable rooms.</div>
        </span>
        <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span>
      </a>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3>What is a room?</h3>
      <p>A room is a chat space you access by visiting a unique link like <em>ahey.net/room</em>. Just click the link and you join the video call right away.</p>

      <h3>What is a private room?</h3>
      <p>All rooms are private by default. This means only people you share the link with can find and join your room. However, if you use an easy-to-guess name, someone might randomly find it. To keep it truly private, use a random name like "81df86c0-6fb5-4bf3-b6e8-14f5d530edad".</p>

      <h3>What is a public room?</h3>
      <p>Public rooms are rooms that start with "@". Anyone can discover these rooms by visiting <a href="/public">ahey.net/public</a> and join them. A new way to meet new people.</p>

      <h3>Is there a maximum number of people who can join a room?</h3>
      <p>Yes. A maximum of 4 people can be in a room at the same time.</p>

      <h3>Why is there a 4-person limit?</h3>
      <p>Ahey connects everyone directly to each other instead of going through a central server. With 4 people, your device is sending and receiving video from 3 other people at the same time. Adding more people would make it too slow and cause quality problems.</p>

      <div class="spacer"></div>
    </section>

    <hr />

    <script type="text/javascript">
      const inputElement = document.querySelector("#roombox input");

      const onJoin = () =>
        window.location.pathname = inputElement.value || "random";


      inputElement.addEventListener("keypress", (e) => {
        if (e.key === "Enter") {
          e.preventDefault();
          onJoin();
        }
      });
    </script>

    <%- include('footer'); -%>
  </div>
</body>

</html>